metadata.name: Cassiopea
metadata.description:
Welcome to these dark and obscure places, explorers.  
If you are here, it is because you are brave. Or desperate. 

In order to explore new worlds, you must be prepared to go to the deepest places. The best hidden. Those shadowy places beneath the earth.  
That's what the Cassiopea ship was created for. 

Inspired by the "Upside-Down" jellyfish, this craft is always pointing downwards. It is able to soften or solidify part of its structure in order to infiltrate the narrowest crevices. 
Its extendable arms constantly analyse and study the surrounding environment, while ensuring increased stability. 

JPEG file - 6580x10000
